StickyListHeaders is an android library that makes it easy to integrate section headers in your ListView. Theses section headers stick to the top like in the new people app of android 4.0 Ice cream sandwich (this can be turned off). 

Use classes in com.emilsjolander.components.StickyListHeaders package in src folder, It is compatible with versions of android down to 2.1.
I have included an apk which is just a compiled version of the code inside the test folder.

HOW TO USE:
Instead of a normal ListView you will want to use StickyListHeadersListViewWrapper, this is a ListView wrapped in a FrameLayout, but style it in xml as you would a normal ListView. Because of this some attributes will be ignored for the framelayout, like padding, margin and background to name a few. Your ListAdapter has to be a subclass of StickyListHeadersAdapter, here you will have to implement getHeaderView(int position, View convertView), getHeaderId(int position) and getView(int position, View convertView).

The headerId indicates when you want to switch header. In an alphabetical list where the first letter is shown in the header you might return the first characters integer values as the headerId for example.


!!GOOD TO KNOW!!
StickyListHeaders do not work together with paddingTop on the listview if you do not specify android:clipToPadding="false" on the listview. this is why i have set this to default.

